data.snippet: Mr. Pranjal Chalise,19 years old Technopreneur from Kathmandu has been awarded the title of ***‚ÄúWai Wai Glocal Teen Hero Nepal 2021‚Äù*** amidst a Virtual Award ceremony organized by Glocal Pvt. Ms. Nona Deprez, the Ambassador of Delegation of the European Union to Nepal, Ms. Vidushi Rana, Director of Marketing, Branding and Business Development at Gold Star shoes, Mr. Varun Chaudhary, Managing Director of CG Corp Global, Mr. Adarsh Avasthi, Country Director of the Coca-Cola Company for Nepal and Mr. Saurabh Jyoti, Director of Jyoti Group of Companiesand today, Mr. Chalise was officially declared and awarded as Wai Wai Glocal Teen Hero Nepal 2021 virtually amidst the awarding ceremony. data.title: Pranjal Chalise - Peer Career Advisor at Amherst College | The Org
data.snippet: # Pranjal Chalise. ### Peer Career Advisor. Pranjal Chalise is a Software Engineer at Microsoft since June 2025, specializing in CoreAI. Concurrently, Pranjal serves as a Peer Career Advisor and a Peer Tutor in both the Math and Computer Science Departments at Amherst College, providing support for students in academic and professional development. Pranjal's prior experience includes working as an AI/ML Fellow and Software Engineer at Microsoft in 2024, and holding various roles at Amherst College such as Math & Stats Student Steering Committee Fellow and IT Specialist. Additionally, Pranjal contributed as a Research Assistant and Research Scholar at Incubate Nepal and is pursuing a Bachelor of Arts in Computer Science and Mathematics at Amherst College, expected to graduate in May 2026. ## Org chart. data.title: Technopreneur Pranjal becomes Teen Hero Nepal 2021 - Mod Dhakal
data.snippet: ### Technopreneur Pranjal becomes Teen Hero Nepal 2021. Pranjal Chalise, 19 years old Technopreneur from Kathmandu, has won the ‚ÄòWai Wai Glocal Teen Hero Nepal 2021‚Äô award. Chalise was selected among the top six finanlists - Anurag Chapagain, 18, Youtuber, from Nawalparasi, Deepak Sutihar, 19, Social Entrepreneur from Saptari, Khusbu Bhandari, 18, Wildlife Conservationist from Chitwan, Neha Gurung, 19, Social Activist from Kathmandu and Sabhya Rai, 19, Education Activist from IIam. Chalise has aided the blind community by inventing Drishti Nepal, which helps visually impaired people in currency bills recognition and cash transactions. Chalise has also initiated a non-profit tech venture E-educators Nepal, which enhances the quality of online education and makes educational resources more accessible. The organiser said that it was the seventh iteration of the Glocal Teen Hero Award, which is the only national platform in Nepal to identify and honour outstanding teenagers whose creativity, commitment, experience, and strong leadership have helped them achieve success in life.
